TY  - JOUR
AU  - Liu, Sheen
AU  - Wu, Chunchi
T1  - Repo Counterparty Risk and On-/Off-the-Run Treasury Spreads
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raw008
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 7
IS  - 1
SP  - 81
EP  - 143
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - We propose a dynamic asset pricing model in which two assets with identical cash flows can trade at different prices not only because of differences in liquidity but counterparty risk. Counterparty risk reduces lenders or borrowers’ willingness to supply funds and collateral, incentives to shortsell and lend, and the likelihood for new bonds to be on special, thereby narrowing on-/off-the-run spreads and affecting asset prices in spot markets. Consistent with this prediction, we find that on-/off-the-run spreads are low when counterparty risk is high and this relationship is much stronger during the financial crisis.Received January 28, 2015; accepted October 4, 2016 by Editor Maureen O' Hara.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raw008
ER  - 



